1.WA Java program to reverse a String
I/p : hello
o/p : olleh
      4 ways to reverse a String
      1.Using toCharArray() method
      2.Using charAt(int index) method
      3.Using java.lang.StringBuffer class provided reverse() method
      4.Using java.lang.StringBuilder class Provided reverse() method
      
      String str = "hello"
      
      h  e l l o
      0  1 2 3 4  --->to find length string have speecial method length()
      
      int length = str.length();
      
      using toCharArray()--- method return character Array
      
      char[] char = str.toCharArray();--->stores data in indexes
      
      we can read the data in reverse
      
      how to read the data from Array ? ---> based on Index
      
      char[4] = o;
      char[3] = l;
      char[2] = l;
      char[1] = e;
      char[0] = h;
      
      we can Access by using indexes 
      now we can use loop to read in reverse
      
      for(int i= char.length-1;i>=0;i--)
      {
         System.out.println(char[i]);
      } 
      
      Approach --2 
      
      Using charAt(int index) -- return object based on index
      
      for(int i=str.length-1;i>=0;i--)
      {
         System.out.print(charAt[i]);
        
      }
      
      Approach -3
      
      
  
       